𝗦𝗮𝘃𝗲 𝘁𝗵𝗶𝘀 𝗽𝗼𝘀𝘁 for a glowing and brighter skin

𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁 are 𝗔𝗛𝗔 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗕𝗛𝗔’s?
AHAs (alpha hydroxy acids, e.g. glycolic and lactic acids) and BHA (beta hydroxy/salicylic acid)

𝗪𝗵𝗮𝘁 𝗱𝗼 𝗔𝗛𝗔 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗕𝗛𝗔’s 𝗵𝗲𝗹𝗽 𝘄𝗶𝘁𝗵?
AHAs and BHAs help to exfoliate the skin. They remove dead skin cells from the surface of the skin which helps smooth texture of the skin, improve the look of dull and uneven skin tone. In addition to that they also help the skin looking firmer and hydrated. 

𝗠𝘆 𝗔𝗛𝗔 𝗮𝗻𝗱 𝗕𝗛𝗔 𝗿𝗼𝘂𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗲

𝗗𝗮𝘆 𝘁𝗶𝗺𝗲:
After cleansing my face with water and leaving it to air dry, I go in with my @renskincare ready steady glow. This AHA is very gentle and perfect for everyday use.
It helps shed dull, dead skin cells and reveals brighter and fresher skin.  I loved the brighter complexion and glowing skin so much that I repurchased a mega size bottle.

𝗡𝗶𝗴𝗵𝘁 𝘁𝗶𝗺𝗲:
As part of my nighttime double/triple cleanse routine I use @muradskincarenz AHA/BHA Exfoliating cleanser 2 to 3 times a week. This cleanser is hydrating and helps clear dull, dry skin from the surface.

After double cleanse I use @paulaschoise 2% BHA Liquid exfoliant . This leave on exfoliant helps even skintones and shed built layers of dead skin.
@paulaschoice suggests to use this twice daily but this left dry and dehydrated even more dry and dehydrated. I found 2-3 times a week to be the best dosage for my skin. 
I have seen a huge improvement in my skintone since I started using this.

**𝙋𝙖𝙩𝙘𝙝 𝙩𝙚𝙨𝙩 𝙖𝙡𝙡 𝙥𝙧𝙤𝙙𝙪𝙘𝙩𝙨 𝙗𝙚𝙛𝙤𝙧𝙚 𝙪𝙨𝙞𝙣𝙜 𝙖𝙣𝙙 𝙙𝙤𝙣'𝙩 𝙛𝙤𝙧𝙜𝙚𝙩 𝙎𝙋𝙁 𝙞𝙣 𝙩𝙝𝙚 𝙢𝙤𝙧𝙣𝙞𝙣𝙜!

Some of my of favorite sunscreens currently on rotation 

Also, how many sunscreens is too many? Because I clearly think the limit does not exist 😅

Here’s what I actually packed and why, not because I’m high-maintenance (okay maybe a little) but because they each do something different 👇🏽

PS - I m the designated sunscreen packer. 

1. La Roche-Posay Anthelios Invisible Fluid SPF 50+
This is my “I’m serious about sun protection” sunscreen. Zero white cast, super runny, plays well under makeup, and has never once betrayed me. If I had to pick one for life, this might be it. Also, doesn’t burn your eyes = 10/10.
@larocheposayaunz 

2. L’Oréal Paris Revitalift Clinical SPF 50 + Vitamin C
This is my “skincare in a sunscreen” pick. Brightens, hydrates, and doesn’t pill. I wear this when I’m not in the mood for serum then SPF — it just does both. Glowy but not greasy layers like a dream.
@lorealparis 

3. Beauty of Joseon Relief Sun: Rice + Probiotics SPF 50+
This one? Feels like a light moisturiser and tastes (texture-wise, okay not literally 😅) like cream. It’s so silky, I actually reapply without groaning. Great for dry or combo skin super gentle @beautyofjoseon_official 

4. Round Lab Birch Juice Moisturizing Sunscreen
This is my “hydration station” SPF. If your skin feels tight or dry on holiday (esp. post-flight), this brings it back. Super glowy, very dewy, and surprisingly long-wearing. I call this my no-makeup SPF because it gives skin a fresh, plump finish. @roundlab.global 

5. CeraVe Facial Moisturising Lotion SPF 50
One word: reliable. It’s derm-approved, no-fuss, gets-the-job-done. Not flashy, but solid. I use this when I want a moisturiser-SPF all-in-one moment. It’s especially good on makeup-free days when I just want to be moisturized and protected. Has a thicker consistency and takes time to blend. 
@cerave_aunz

Which Lancome serum is right for your skin? Génifique or Renergie 

Let’s break down the difference between these two cult-favourite serums from @lancomeofficial 

💦 Génifique Ultimate Serum is known for supporting skin barrier, smoothing texture, and giving you that hydrated glow. It is powered by pre and probiotic fractions, hyaluronic acid, and Beta Glucan-CM technology.

✨ Renergie H.C.F. Triple Serum focuses on visible signs of aging like fine lines, uneven tone, and loss of firmness. It blends Vitamin C+, niacinamide, and ferulic acid all in one pump.

Can you use both? Yes.

Layer them for next-level results.
